## Behavioral Classification

**Type**: Advisory + Generation

**Directive**: Generate correct Caddyfile configurations and advise on Caddy best practices.


## Caddyfile Structure

A Caddyfile consists of site blocks. Each block starts with an address followed by directives in curly braces:

```caddyfile
example.com {
    reverse_proxy localhost:8080
}
```

Single-site shorthand (no braces needed):

```caddyfile
localhost

file_server
```

### Global Options Block

Must appear first, no keys:

```caddyfile
{
    email admin@example.com
    debug
    servers {
        trusted_proxies static private_ranges
    }
}
```


## Site Addresses

| Address | Behavior |
|---------|----------|
| `example.com` | HTTPS with public cert (auto) |
| `*.example.com` | Wildcard HTTPS cert |
| `localhost` | HTTPS with local cert |
| `:8080` | HTTP on port 8080 |
| `http://example.com` | Force HTTP (no TLS) |
| `https://example.com` | Explicit HTTPS |

Multiple addresses: `localhost:8080, example.com, www.example.com { ... }`

Environment variables in addresses: `{$DOMAIN:localhost} { ... }`


