## Common Patterns

### Reverse Proxy

```caddyfile
example.com {
    reverse_proxy localhost:9000
}
```

With load balancing:

```caddyfile
example.com {
    reverse_proxy app-01:8080 app-02:8080 {
        lb_policy round_robin
        health_uri /health
        health_interval 10s
    }
}
```

With header manipulation:

```caddyfile
example.com {
    reverse_proxy localhost:9000 {
        header_up Host {upstream_hostport}
        header_up X-Real-IP {remote_host}
        header_up X-Forwarded-For {remote_host}
    }
}
```

### Static File Server

```caddyfile
example.com {
    root * /var/www/html
    file_server
}
```

With directory browsing:

```caddyfile
example.com {
    root * /var/www/html
    file_server browse
}
```

### SPA (Single Page Application)

```caddyfile
example.com {
    root * /var/www/app
    try_files {path} /index.html
    file_server
}
```

### API + SPA Combined

```caddyfile
example.com {
    handle /api/* {
        reverse_proxy localhost:8080
    }
    handle {
        root * /var/www/app
        try_files {path} /index.html
        file_server
    }
}
```

### HTTPS Redirect + WWW Redirect

```caddyfile
www.example.com {
    redir https://example.com{uri} permanent
}

example.com {
    reverse_proxy localhost:8080
}
```

### Compression

```caddyfile
example.com {
    encode zstd gzip
    file_server
}
```

### Security Headers

```caddyfile
example.com {
    header {
        Strict-Transport-Security "max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload"
        X-Content-Type-Options "nosniff"
        X-Frame-Options "DENY"
        Referrer-Policy "strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
        -Server
    }
    reverse_proxy localhost:8080
}
```

### Logging

```caddyfile
example.com {
    log {
        output file /var/log/caddy/access.log {
            roll_size 100MiB
            roll_keep 5
        }
        format json
    }
    reverse_proxy localhost:8080
}
```

### PHP (WordPress example)

```caddyfile
example.com {
    root * /var/www/wordpress
    encode gzip
    php_fastcgi unix//run/php/php-fpm.sock
    file_server
}
```


## Matchers

Filter which requests a directive applies to:

```caddyfile
# Path matcher (inline)
reverse_proxy /api/* localhost:8080

# Wildcard (all requests)
root * /var/www

# Named matcher
@post {
    method POST
}
reverse_proxy @post localhost:9001

# Combined conditions
@websockets {
    header Connection *Upgrade*
    header Upgrade websocket
}
reverse_proxy @websockets localhost:6001
```


## Snippets

Reusable config blocks:

```caddyfile
(logging) {
    log {
        output file /var/log/caddy/{args[0]}.log
        format json
    }
}

example.com {
    import logging example
    reverse_proxy localhost:8080
}
```


## Named Routes

```caddyfile
&(app-proxy) {
    reverse_proxy app-01:8080 app-02:8080
}

example.com {
    invoke app-proxy
}
```


## Environment Variables

Substituted before Caddyfile parsing:

```caddyfile
{$DOMAIN:localhost} {
    reverse_proxy {$BACKEND:localhost:8080}
}
```

Runtime substitution via placeholders: `{env.API_KEY}`


